data.description: Beautiful Victorian in the Green Ridge Section of Scranton.  Upon entering from the front foyer you are greeted by a grand staircase, decorative fireplace, and exquisite woodwork throughout.  Formal living room features original pocket doors leading into the formal dining room.  Glass French doors on the opposite side of the dining room lead you into a very large family room.  Kitchen with eat-in area and a full bathroom complete the main level.  You'll find three generous sized bedrooms (one with a balcony) and another full bathroom on the second level.  Head upstairs from floor two to find a partially finished third with an additional fourth bedroom and an attic storage room that could easily be converted into a fifth bedroom or whatever additional space you imagine.  The partially finished basement houses an office and laundry space plus a very large bonus area that was once used as a game room and home bar but is now used as storage.  Outside you'll find a large, long driveway with wrought iron gate, landscaping, massive deck with above ground pool encased, a spa, and ample outdoor living/entertaining space.  This large home has everything you need with the possibilities for so much more and is centrally located to all Scranton has to offer., Baths: 1 Bath Lev 1,1 Bath Lev 2, Beds: 2+ Bed 2nd,Mstr 2nd, SqFt Fin - Main: 979.92, SqFt Fin - 3rd: 140.88, Tax Information: Available, Formal Dining Room: Y, SqFt Fin - 2nd: 543.38, Additional Info: All information and measurements are approximate and are not warranted or guaranteed.
